<h3>About FilmTag {version}</h3>

<p>Basic Android app for keeping track of photography settings while shooting analog film. As used by
analog photographers who can't rely on exif information when using analog roll film while shooting.</p>

<h3>Goals</h3>

<p>Keep it dead simple and easy to use. The photographer shouldn't have to look into settings or any
complex editing options while shooting. Keep distraction to an absolute minimum.</p>

<h3>Key features</h3>

<p>
* get a list of film rolls created<br/>
* create a new film roll adding film type, nr of frames and ISO exposed at (!film ISO)<br/>
* show details (frames) for each of these film rolls (+ delete option on detail screen)<br/>
* from details change the aperture, shutter and notes for each frame<br/>
</p>

<h3>Project</h3>

<p>Source code available on bitbucket, see: <a href="https://bitbucket.org/cappelleh/filmtag/">https://bitbucket.org/cappelleh/filmtag/</a></p>
